## Unit 1 – Introduction to Security and Risk Management

### Unit Overview  
Unit 1 introduces core definitions and concepts of security and risk management, including common definitions of risk, threats, and vulnerabilities. It explains how risk assessments are structured and why understanding risk terminology is essential before applying qualitative or quantitative methods. These foundational concepts lay the basis for later units.

