### Individual Contribution
I authored the initial discussion post on risk definitions and responded to at least two peers using references from ISO 31000 and academic sources. I also contributed to the Module Wiki by defining terminology relevant to Unit 1.

### Critical Reflection  
Unit 1 helped me understand that risk is not just a chance of loss, but the *effect of uncertainty on objectives*, as defined in ISO 31000. This distinction between probability and impact made me appreciate the complexity of the risk management process and why consistent terminology is essential. Early engagement with peers through discussion reinforced that operationalising these definitions requires careful thought and shared understanding. This reflective start shaped my approach to risk modelling in later units.

